                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Etc/UTC"
                    },
                    "body": ">\u00a0The idea of \"const\" files is a bit murky in itself\u00a0:)\r\n\r\nTrue in general.\u00a0I'm not completely sure if mmap'ed files are different enough to make an exception, but at least from the technical PoW you could get their size as a const operation. Thinking about it, the Read(int, shared_ptr<Buffer>*) method could also have a const version.\u00a0\r\n\r\nIt came up when I tried to pass a const MemoryMappedFile& to a function. Surely I can just pass a pointer, but it feels strange to do it for a read-only file, especially\u00a0when there isn't any seeking involved.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
